HEADWORD: Sporozoa
<hw>Spo`ro*zo"a</hw> <pr>(-z⟦omac⟧"⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>spo`ros</grk> a spore + <grk>zw^,on</grk> an
animal.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extensive division of
parasitic Protozoa, which increase by sporulation. It includes the
Gregarinida.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

